# Setup GTR

## Overview

Install gtr and configure with DLC-compatible defaults.

**Announce at start:** "I'm setting up gtr for worktree management."

## Check Installation

```bash
git gtr --version 2>/dev/null && echo "gtr installed" || echo "gtr not found"
```

## Install

```bash
cd /tmp
git clone https://github.com/coderabbitai/git-worktree-runner.git
```

Then ask the user to run the install script (requires sudo):

```
I've cloned gtr to /tmp/git-worktree-runner.

Please run the install script (requires sudo):
  cd /tmp/git-worktree-runner && ./install.sh

Let me know when it's done and I'll verify the installation.
```

After user confirms, verify:

```bash
git gtr --version
```

## Configure Global Defaults

**Note:** Use absolute paths for global config (tilde `~` is not expanded).

```bash
# Worktree directory (use $HOME for expansion)
git gtr config set gtr.worktrees.dir "$HOME/worktrees" --global

# Files to copy to new worktrees (multi-value, use add for each)
git gtr config add gtr.copy.include ".env" --global
git gtr config add gtr.copy.include ".env.local" --global
git gtr config add gtr.copy.include "*.local.md" --global
git gtr config add gtr.copy.include ".claude/*.local.md" --global

# Post-create hook (runs after worktree creation)
git gtr config set gtr.hook.postCreate "just install" --global

# Default editor (customize to your preference: code, cursor, vim, etc.)
git gtr config set gtr.editor.default code --global

# Default AI tool
git gtr config set gtr.ai.default claude --global
```

**Key settings:**
- `gtr.copy.include` - Copies .env and config files to new worktrees (essential for secrets/settings)
- `gtr.hook.postCreate` - Runs `just install` to set up dependencies
- `gtr.worktrees.dir` - Standard location for all worktrees

## Repository Configuration

Create `.gtrconfig` in repository root for team defaults.

**Note:** Use relative paths in `.gtrconfig` (user-agnostic).

```ini
[worktrees]
    dir = ../worktrees

[copy]
    include = .env
    include = .env.local
    include = *.local.md
    include = .claude/*.local.md

[hook]
    postCreate = just install

[editor]
    default = code

[ai]
    default = claude
```

## Verify

```bash
git gtr config list
git gtr doctor
```

## Output

```
gtr installed and configured:
- Worktree directory: ~/worktrees/ (global) or ../worktrees (repo)
- Copy files: .env, .env.local, *.local.md, .claude/*.local.md
- Post-create hook: just install
- Editor: code (customize with gtr.editor.default)
- AI tool: claude
```
